        {
          "title": "Joy",
          "year": 2015
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "'Alien: Romulus'",
      "note": "an effective mid-tier genre movie",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Alien: Romulus",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Fede Alvarez's entry, set between 'Alien' and 'Aliens': space-colony pirates raid a derelict station and find facehuggers. Cailee Spaeny (Rain) and David Jonsson (Andy, the malfunctioning synthetic who reboots into a decisive one) anchor it; both hosts rate the practical sets, the acid-blood zero-G ballet, the elevator-shaft chase, and a body-horror fourth act. Their reservations: a CGI Ian Holm resurrected as the synthetic Rook, and 'get away from her, you bitch'-style fan service they found more processed than earned."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "ranking",
      "heading": "The 'Alien' Movie Rankings",
      "note": "best to worst",
      "subject": "Alien",
      "ranked": true,
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Alien",
          "year": 1979,
          "note": "No. 1 for both. Sean: 'one of my favorite films ever made.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Aliens",
          "year": 1986,
          "note": "The narrow runner-up. Sean gripes that the grain-scrubbed 4K reissue makes the sets look constructed rather than lived-in."
        },
        {
          "title": "Prometheus",
          "year": 2012,
          "note": "The consensus No. 3, buoyed by the abortion-bay body horror and Ridley Scott's Jesus-was-an-engineer lore."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien: Covenant",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "'First 45 minutes is perfect,' plus a Fassbender David performance that makes you want more of the aborted David trilogy."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien 3",
          "year": 1992,
          "note": "Fincher's compromised debut; Charles Dance gives a favorite franchise performance, but Chris still ranks it dead last on his personal list."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien: Romulus",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Slots in above Resurrection after a single viewing; fun, not as idea-rich as the two before it."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien Resurrection",
          "year": 1997,
          "note": "The underwater sequence is great, but the Jeunet pitch of wide-eyed yelling grates and clashes with Whedon's dialogue."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien vs. Predator",
          "year": 2004,
          "note": "'Probably the second worst movie ever made' featuring an alien; effectively not canon."
        },
        {
          "title": "Alien vs. Predator: Requiem",
          "year": 2007,
          "note": "Declared the worst movie ever made featuring an alien."
        }
      ]
    },
